dbpedia.org/resource/Chile_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chile_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's hard to separate them, but in the men's we just have to start with the reigning Olympic gold medalist Latvia.\\u00c2  They want to go back-to-back in Paris and in Hong Kong they will bring three Latvian legends who made history in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 872, \"to\": 1108, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1021, \"end\": 1026, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999680571824, \"rank\": 3.194298167753607e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1034, \"end\": 1043, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.737813464539394, \"rank\": 0.3552433852829905, \"text\": \"Hong Kong\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1066, \"end\": 1073, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Latvia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999745341, \"rank\": 2.3864787197877357e-11, \"text\": \"Latvian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Latvia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Latvia\"}, {\"begin\": 1102, \"end\": 1107, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9995232384890859, \"rank\": 0.00047677011706212747, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Superheroes Karlis Lasmanis and Nauris Miezis will put on their capes, while Edgar Krumins will be doing all the little things to inspire his team.\\u00c2  No.1 seed Netherlands are worthy of the hype because they have a Dutch hoops legend who has made the half-court his home.\", \"from\": 1109, \"to\": 1380, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1141, \"end\": 1154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nauris_Miezis\", \"score\": 0.999999996610768, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nauris Miezis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nauris_Miezis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nauris_Miezis\"}, {\"begin\": 1269, \"end\": 1280, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9938213458558687, \"rank\": 0.0059867202480435675, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}, {\"begin\": 1324, \"end\": 1329, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9989455324403487, \"rank\": 0.000606482289494799, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Worthy de Jong is his name - but you knew that already - and he will be out to lead the Netherlands to an Olympic berth.\\u00c2  A post shared by FIBA3x3 (@fiba3x3)  \\u00c2  Mongolia showed off their depth of talent at theFIBA 3x3 Asia Cup 2024with a bronze medal performance.\", \"from\": 1381, \"to\": 1646, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1381, \"end\": 1395, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Worthy_de_Jong\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Worthy de Jong\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Worthy_de_Jong\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Worthy_de_Jong\"}, {\"begin\": 1469, \"end\": 1480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9938213458558687, \"rank\": 0.0059867202480435675, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They were superbly led by sniper Anand Ariunbold, who returns for a full-strength Mongolia.\\u00c2  Austria and Switzerland have a slew of players who dominate the World Tour.\", \"from\": 1647, \"to\": 1816, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1680, \"end\": 1685, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Viswanathan_Anand\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4689801067252725e-13, \"text\": \"Anand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Viswanathan_Anand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Viswanathan_Anand\"}, {\"begin\": 1741, \"end\": 1748, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austria_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.7601354163199013, \"rank\": 0.31555506888941154, \"text\": \"Austria\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austria_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austria_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1753, \"end\": 1764, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"score\": 0.9728473280018906, \"rank\": 0.01952760839308324, \"text\": \"Switzerland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"None more so than speedsters Nico\\u00c2\\u00a0Kaltenbrunner and Gilles Martin, who are capable of magic tricks with the Wilson as they look to show off their insane skills on the biggest stage in sports.\\u00c2  In the women's, reigning European champs the Netherlands look formidable and they will bring a lot of size to Hong Kong.\", \"from\": 1817, \"to\": 2132, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1877, \"end\": 1883, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\", \"score\": 0.9997521777907409, \"rank\": 0.00024788363003924756, \"text\": \"Martin\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\"}, {\"begin\": 1926, \"end\": 1932, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woodrow_Wilson\", \"score\": 0.8661676368425112, \"rank\": 0.13028874345991992, \"text\": \"Wilson\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woodrow_Wilson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woodrow_Wilson\"}, {\"begin\": 2057, \"end\": 2068, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9938213458558687, \"rank\": 0.0059867202480435675, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}, {\"begin\": 2122, \"end\": 2131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.737813464539394, \"rank\": 0.3552433852829905, \"text\": \"Hong Kong\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is no more dominant interior presence than Noortje Driessen, who always rises to the challenge.\\u00c2  \\u00c2  No.1 seed Hungary will be out to show why they have got top billing, while Mongolia will arrive in Hong Kong with swagger after an emotional bronze medal victory at the Asia Cup.\\u00c2  Khulan Onolbaatar is the pride of her nation, but her inspirational deeds are matched by Egypt star\\u00c2\\u00a0Soraya Mohamed who can make opponents look foolish after she taps into her deep bag.\\u00c2  A post shared by FIBA3x3 (@fiba3x3)  \\u00c2  The Field  As you would expect, there are plenty of dark horses in the men's led by African champs Egypt, who will rely on\\u00c2\\u00a0Ahmed Mohamed for buckets.\", \"from\": 2133, \"to\": 2799, \"entiti